# Float8 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: float8)')
!tx 'insert (1.9e308) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `FLOAT8`
>   1 │ insert (1.9e308) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `1.9e308` does not fit into `FLOAT8` (range: -1.8e308 to +1.8e308)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `FLOAT8`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
